This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for training neural networks using variational inference. The paper also discusses the use of this method in regression benchmarks, active learning, and reinforcement learning, which are all topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. 

Additionally, the paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a method for improving uncertainty estimates in neural networks, which is an important aspect of AI systems. 

The paper also discusses the use of the method in convolutional neural networks (ConvNets), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the use of the method in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of AI that involves training agents to make decisions in an environment. Therefore, it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
